{"timestamp": "2026-05-23 10:45:06,415", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-23T10:45:06.415451\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop match detection and scoring: Tetris line clears, Bejeweled match-3 detection, chain reaction logic and bonus point calculation\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\n\\n# Define colors\\nCOLORS = {\\n    \\\"red\\\": (255, 0, 0),\\n    \\\"green\\\": (0, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"blue\\\": (0, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"yellow\\\": (255, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"cyan\\\": (0, 255, 255),\\n    \\\"magenta\\\": (255, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"orange\\\": (255, 165, 0),\\n    \\\"gray\\\": (128, 128, 128)\\n}\\n\\n# Tetromino definitions\\nTETROMINOS = {\\n    \\\"I\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1,1,1]],             \\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\"},\\n    \\\"J\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,0,0],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"blue\\\"},\\n    \\\"L\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,0,1],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The Bejeweled match-3 detection compares `Gem` objects directly, but since each `Gem` is a unique instance, `grid[y][x] == grid[y][x+1]` will almost always be False. You need to compare their `color_name` instead.\\n2. The current `check_match_3` only finds runs of exactly 3 and can miss longer runs or produce duplicate positions. It’s better to scan for runs of length ≥3 both horizontally and vertically.\\n3. There is no chain reaction logic: you need to repeatedly clear lines and matches until none remain, counting each round as a chain step.\\n4. The scoring function includes a chain bonus, but there is no wrapper function that invokes scoring per chain step and aggregates the total score.\\n5. The task requested a single entry point for match detection and scoring that returns lines-cleared, gems-cleared, chain count, and total score in one call.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\ndef check_line_clears(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check for and clear full horizontal lines.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    lines_to_clear = [i for i, row in enumerate(grid) if all(cell is not None for cell in row)]\\n    for row_index in reversed(lines_to_clear):\\n        del grid[row_index]\\n        grid.insert(0, [None] * GRID_WIDTH)\\n    return len(lines_to_clear)\\n\\n\\ndef check_match_3(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Find and clear runs of >=3 same-colored gems.\\n    Returns number of gems cleared.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    to_clear = [[False]*GRID_WIDTH for _ in range(GRID_HEIGHT)]\\n\\n    # Horizontal runs\\n    for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n        x = 0\\n        while x < GRID_WIDTH:\\n            cell = grid[y][x]\\n            if cell is None:\\n                x += 1\\n                continue\\n            color = cell.color_name\\n            length = 1\\n            for k in range(x+1, GRID_WIDTH):\\n                if grid[y][k] is not None and grid[y][k].color_name == color:\\n                    length += 1\\n                else:\\n                    break\\n            if length >= 3:\\n                for k in range(x, x+length):\\n                    to_clear[y][k] = True\\n            x += length\\n\\n    # Vertical runs\\n    for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n        y = 0\\n        while y < GRID_HEIGHT:\\n            cell = grid[y][x]\\n            if cell is None:\\n                y += 1\\n                continue\\n            color = cell.color_name\\n            length = 1\\n            for k in range(y+1, GRID_HEIGHT):\\n                if grid[k][x] is not None and grid[k][x].color_name == color:\\n                    length += 1\\n                else:\\n                    break\\n            if length >= 3:\\n                for k in range(y, y+length):\\n                    to_clear[k][x] = True\\n            y += length\\n\\n    # Clear and count\\n    cleared = 0\\n    for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n        for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n            if to_clear[y][x]:\\n                grid[y][x] = None\\n                cleared += 1\\n\\n    # Apply gravity per column\\n    for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n        stack = [grid[y][x] for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT) if grid[y][x] is not None]\\n        for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT-1, -1, -1):\\n            grid[y][x] = stack.pop() if stack else None\\n\\n    return cleared\\n\\n\\ndef calculate_score(lines_cleared, gems_cleared, chain_reaction_level):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Calculate score. chain_reaction_level=0 for initial clear,\\n    1 for first chain, etc.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Simple Tetris scoring: 1 line=100, 2=300, 3=500, 4=800\\n    tetris_scores = {1:100, 2:300, 3:500, 4:800}\\n    line_score = tetris_scores.get(lines_cleared, lines_cleared * 200)\\n    gem_score  = gems_cleared * 50\\n    chain_bonus = chain_reaction_level * 25\\n    return line_score + gem_score + chain_bonus\\n\\n\\ndef process_clears(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Perform line clears and match-3 clears until no more are possible.\\n    Returns: (total_lines_cleared, total_gems_cleared, chain_count, total_score)\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    total_lines = 0\\n    total_gems = 0\\n    total_score = 0\\n    chain = 0\\n\\n    while True:\\n        lines = check_line_clears(grid)\\n        gems = check_match_3(grid)\\n        if lines == 0 and gems == 0:\\n            break\\n        # First clear has chain_reaction_level=0, next is 1, etc.\\n        chain_reaction_level = max(0, chain)\\n        score = calculate_score(lines, gems, chain_reaction_level)\\n        total_lines += lines\\n        total_gems += gems\\n        total_score += score\\n        chain += 1\\n\\n    return total_lines, total_gems, chain, total_score\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-23 10:45:17,680", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nDevelop a game that fuses Tetris and Bejeweled mechanics. \\nThis game needs to add keyboard control function.\\nFalling tetrominoes should lock into a grid and transform into colored gems. \\nThe game must support both Tetris line-clearing and Bejeweled match-3 clearing, triggering chain reactions and bonus points. \\nInclude a GUI (using a framework like Pygame) that displays the game grid, current score, and next tetromino preview, along with smooth animations. \\nNo sound effects are needed.\\n\\nOutput Format: python\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Define core data structures: game grid representation and tetromino shape/color definitions\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\n\\n# Define colors\\nCOLORS = {\\n    \\\"red\\\": (255, 0, 0),\\n    \\\"green\\\": (0, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"blue\\\": (0, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"yellow\\\": (255, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"cyan\\\": (0, 255, 255),\\n    \\\"magenta\\\": (255, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"orange\\\": (255, 165, 0),\\n    \\\"gray\\\": (128, 128, 128)\\n}\\n\\nCOLOR_LIST = list(COLORS.keys())\\n\\n\\n# Define Tetromino shapes and colors\\nTETROMINOS = {\\n    \\\"I\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1, 1, 1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\"},\\n    \\\"J\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1, 0, 0], [1, 1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"blue\\\"},\\n    \\\"L\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0, 0, 1], [1, 1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"orange\\\"},\\n    \\\"O\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1, 1], [1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"yellow\\\"},\\n    \\\"S\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0, 1, 1], [1, 1, 0]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\"},\\n    \\\"T\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0, 1, 0], [1, 1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"magenta\\\"},\\n    \\\"Z\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1, 1, 0], [0, 1, 1]], \\\"color\\\": \\\"red\\\"}\\n}\\n\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    def __init__(self, x, y, shape, color):\\n        self.x = x\\n        self.y = y\\n        self.shape = shape\\n        self.color = color\\n\\n    def rotate(self):\\n        # Rotate the shape 90 degrees clockwise\\n        rotated_shape = list(zip(*self.shape[::-1]))\\n        self.shape = [list(row) for row in rotated_shape]\\n\\n\\n# Game grid dimensions\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\n# Initialize the game grid with None values\\ndef create_grid(width, height):\\n    return [[None for _ in range(width)] for _ in range(height)]\\n\\n# Example of initializing the grid\\ngrid = create_grid(GRID_WIDTH, GRID_HEIGHT)\\n```\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Implement tetromino behavior: rotation, horizontal movement, gravity drop, locking into grid and conversion to colored gems\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\n\\n# Define colors\\nCOLORS = {\\n    \\\"red\\\": (255, 0, 0),\\n    \\\"green\\\": (0, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"blue\\\": (0, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"yellow\\\": (255, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"cyan\\\": (0, 255, 255),\\n    \\\"magenta\\\": (255, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"orange\\\": (255, 165, 0),\\n    \\\"gray\\\": (128, 128, 128)\\n}\\n\\n# Tetromino definitions\\nTETROMINOS = {\\n    \\\"I\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1,1,1]],             \\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\"},\\n    \\\"J\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,0,0],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"blue\\\"},\\n    \\\"L\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,0,1],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"orange\\\"},\\n    \\\"O\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1],[1,1]],           \\\"color\\\": \\\"yellow\\\"},\\n    \\\"S\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,1,1],[1,1,0]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\"},\\n    \\\"T\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,1,0],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"magenta\\\"},\\n    \\\"Z\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1,0],[0,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"red\\\"}\\n}\\n\\nGRID_WIDTH  = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\nclass Gem:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"A single colored gem in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, color_name):\\n        self.color_name = color_name\\n        self.rgb = COLORS[color_name]\\n\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    def __init__(self, shape, color_name, x=3, y=0):\\n        self.shape = [row[:] for row in shape]\\n        self.color = color_name\\n        self.x = x\\n        self.y = y\\n\\n    def _rotate_shape(self):\\n        return [list(row) for row in zip(*self.shape[::-1])]\\n\\n    def rotate(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Attempt to rotate; revert if invalid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_shape = self.shape\\n        self.shape = self._rotate_shape()\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.shape = old_shape\\n\\n    def move(self, dx, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Attempt horizontal move; revert if invalid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_x = self.x\\n        self.x += dx\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.x = old_x\\n\\n    def soft_drop(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Move down one; return False if it would collide.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_y = self.y\\n        self.y += 1\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.y = old_y\\n            return False\\n        return True\\n\\n    def hard_drop(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Drop until collision; lock in place at the end.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        while self.soft_drop(grid):\\n            pass\\n        return False  # indicates it landed\\n\\ndef create_grid(width, height):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Initialize empty grid of specified size.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return [[None for _ in range(width)] for _ in range(height)]\\n\\ndef is_valid_position(tetromino, grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check if tetromino is within bounds and not colliding.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    for dy, row in enumerate(tetromino.shape):\\n        for dx, cell in enumerate(row):\\n            if cell:\\n                x = tetromino.x + dx\\n                y = tetromino.y + dy\\n                if x < 0 or x >= GRID_WIDTH or y < 0 or y >= GRID_HEIGHT:\\n                    return False\\n                if grid[y][x] is not None:\\n                    return False\\n    return True\\n\\ndef lock_tetromino(tetromino, grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert all occupied cells of the tetromino into Gems in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    for dy, row in enumerate(tetromino.shape):\\n        for dx, cell in enumerate(row):\\n            if cell:\\n                x = tetromino.x + dx\\n                y = tetromino.y + dy\\n                if 0 <= x < GRID_WIDTH and 0 <= y < GRID_HEIGHT:\\n                    grid[y][x] = Gem(tetromino.color)\\n\\nclass TetrominoManager:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Manages active tetromino, spawning, and locking.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, grid):\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n\\n    def _spawn_new(self):\\n        key = random.choice(list(TETROMINOS.keys()))\\n        data = TETROMINOS[key]\\n        # center initial x so shape appears roughly in middle\\n        start_x = (GRID_WIDTH - len(data[\\\"shape\\\"][0])) // 2\\n        return Tetromino(data[\\\"shape\\\"], data[\\\"color\\\"], x=start_x, y=0)\\n\\n    def update(self, command=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        command: one of 'left','right','rotate','soft_drop','hard_drop'\\n        Returns True if piece locked (and a new spawn occurred).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if command == 'left':\\n            self.current.move(-1, self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'right':\\n            self.current.move(1, self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'rotate':\\n            self.current.rotate(self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'soft_drop':\\n            landed = not self.current.soft_drop(self.grid)\\n            if landed:\\n                lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n                self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n                return True\\n        elif command == 'hard_drop':\\n            self.current.hard_drop(self.grid)\\n            lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n            self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n            return True\\n        else:\\n            # gravity tick\\n            landed = not self.current.soft_drop(self.grid)\\n            if landed:\\n                lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n                self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n                return True\\n        return False\\n```\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop match detection and scoring: Tetris line clears, Bejeweled match-3 detection, chain reaction logic and bonus point calculation\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\n\\n# Define colors\\nCOLORS = {\\n    \\\"red\\\": (255, 0, 0),\\n    \\\"green\\\": (0, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"blue\\\": (0, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"yellow\\\": (255, 255, 0),\\n    \\\"cyan\\\": (0, 255, 255),\\n    \\\"magenta\\\": (255, 0, 255),\\n    \\\"orange\\\": (255, 165, 0),\\n    \\\"gray\\\": (128, 128, 128)\\n}\\n\\n# Tetromino definitions\\nTETROMINOS = {\\n    \\\"I\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1,1,1]],             \\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\"},\\n    \\\"J\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,0,0],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"blue\\\"},\\n    \\\"L\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,0,1],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"orange\\\"},\\n    \\\"O\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1],[1,1]],           \\\"color\\\": \\\"yellow\\\"},\\n    \\\"S\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,1,1],[1,1,0]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\"},\\n    \\\"T\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[0,1,0],[1,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"magenta\\\"},\\n    \\\"Z\\\": {\\\"shape\\\": [[1,1,0],[0,1,1]],       \\\"color\\\": \\\"red\\\"}\\n}\\n\\nGRID_WIDTH  = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\nclass Gem:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"A single colored gem in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, color_name):\\n        self.color_name = color_name\\n        self.rgb = COLORS[color_name]\\n\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    def __init__(self, shape, color_name, x=3, y=0):\\n        self.shape = [row[:] for row in shape]\\n        self.color = color_name\\n        self.x = x\\n        self.y = y\\n\\n    def _rotate_shape(self):\\n        return [list(row) for row in zip(*self.shape[::-1])]\\n\\n    def rotate(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Attempt to rotate; revert if invalid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_shape = self.shape\\n        self.shape = self._rotate_shape()\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.shape = old_shape\\n\\n    def move(self, dx, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Attempt horizontal move; revert if invalid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_x = self.x\\n        self.x += dx\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.x = old_x\\n\\n    def soft_drop(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Move down one; return False if it would collide.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        old_y = self.y\\n        self.y += 1\\n        if not is_valid_position(self, grid):\\n            self.y = old_y\\n            return False\\n        return True\\n\\n    def hard_drop(self, grid):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Drop until collision; lock in place at the end.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        while self.soft_drop(grid):\\n            pass\\n        return False  # indicates it landed\\n\\ndef create_grid(width, height):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Initialize empty grid of specified size.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return [[None for _ in range(width)] for _ in range(height)]\\n\\ndef is_valid_position(tetromino, grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check if tetromino is within bounds and not colliding.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    for dy, row in enumerate(tetromino.shape):\\n        for dx, cell in enumerate(row):\\n            if cell:\\n                x = tetromino.x + dx\\n                y = tetromino.y + dy\\n                if x < 0 or x >= GRID_WIDTH or y < 0 or y >= GRID_HEIGHT:\\n                    return False\\n                if grid[y][x] is not None:\\n                    return False\\n    return True\\n\\ndef lock_tetromino(tetromino, grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert all occupied cells of the tetromino into Gems in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    for dy, row in enumerate(tetromino.shape):\\n        for dx, cell in enumerate(row):\\n            if cell:\\n                x = tetromino.x + dx\\n                y = tetromino.y + dy\\n                if 0 <= x < GRID_WIDTH and 0 <= y < GRID_HEIGHT:\\n                    grid[y][x] = Gem(tetromino.color)\\n\\nclass TetrominoManager:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Manages active tetromino, spawning, and locking.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, grid):\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n\\n    def _spawn_new(self):\\n        key = random.choice(list(TETROMINOS.keys()))\\n        data = TETROMINOS[key]\\n        # center initial x so shape appears roughly in middle\\n        start_x = (GRID_WIDTH - len(data[\\\"shape\\\"][0])) // 2\\n        return Tetromino(data[\\\"shape\\\"], data[\\\"color\\\"], x=start_x, y=0)\\n\\n    def update(self, command=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        command: one of 'left','right','rotate','soft_drop','hard_drop'\\n        Returns True if piece locked (and a new spawn occurred).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if command == 'left':\\n            self.current.move(-1, self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'right':\\n            self.current.move(1, self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'rotate':\\n            self.current.rotate(self.grid)\\n        elif command == 'soft_drop':\\n            landed = not self.current.soft_drop(self.grid)\\n            if landed:\\n                lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n                self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n                return True\\n        elif command == 'hard_drop':\\n            self.current.hard_drop(self.grid)\\n            lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n            self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n            return True\\n        else:\\n            # gravity tick\\n            landed = not self.current.soft_drop(self.grid)\\n            if landed:\\n                lock_tetromino(self.current, self.grid)\\n                self.current = self._spawn_new()\\n                return True\\n        return False\\n\\ndef check_line_clears(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check for and clear full horizontal lines.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    lines_to_clear = []\\n    for i, row in enumerate(grid):\\n        if all(row):  # all cells are gems\\n            lines_to_clear.append(i)\\n\\n    for row_index in lines_to_clear:\\n        del grid[row_index]\\n        grid.insert(0, [None] * GRID_WIDTH)  # Add empty row at top\\n    return len(lines_to_clear)  # Return number of lines cleared\\n\\ndef check_match_3(grid):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check for and clear Bejeweled-style match-3.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    matches = []\\n\\n    # Horizontal matches\\n    for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n        for x in range(GRID_WIDTH - 2):\\n            if (grid[y][x] is not None and\\n                grid[y][x] == grid[y][x+1] and\\n                grid[y][x] == grid[y][x+2]):\\n                matches.append(((x, y), (x+1, y), (x+2, y)))\\n\\n    # Vertical matches\\n    for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n        for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT - 2):\\n            if (grid[y][x] is not None and\\n                grid[y][x] == grid[y+1][x] and\\n                grid[y][x] == grid[y+2][x]):\\n                matches.append(((x, y), (x, y+1), (x, y+2)))\\n\\n    # Remove duplicates and clear matches\\n    cleared_positions = set()\\n    for match in matches:\\n        for x, y in match:\\n            cleared_positions.add((x, y))\\n\\n    # Convert to list for easier manipulation\\n    cleared_positions = list(cleared_positions)\\n\\n    # Clear the matched gems from the grid\\n    for x, y in cleared_positions:\\n        grid[y][x] = None\\n\\n    # Apply gravity to move gems down\\n    for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n        # Move empty spaces to the top\\n        empty_count = 0\\n        for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n            if grid[y][x] is None:\\n                empty_count += 1\\n            elif empty_count > 0:\\n                grid[y - empty_count][x] = grid[y][x]\\n                grid[y][x] = None\\n\\n    return len(cleared_positions)\\n\\ndef calculate_score(lines_cleared, gems_cleared, chain_reaction_level):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculate score based on lines cleared and gems cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    line_clear_score = lines_cleared * (100 * lines_cleared)  # Tetris scoring\\n    gem_clear_score  = gems_cleared * 50  # Bejeweled scoring\\n    chain_bonus      = chain_reaction_level * 25 # Bonus for chain reactions\\n\\n    return line_clear_score + gem_clear_score + chain_bonus\\n```\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Implement next tetromino preview logic and integrate preview data into game state\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\n\\n# Constants\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\nCELL_SIZE = 30\\nSCREEN_W